  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate speech understanding in simulated reverberant
      environments with MED-EL cochlear implant recipients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study will determine if electrode length and coding strategy effect performance. We will
      also study performance over time with new recipients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
